27/07/2005
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Damage from the recent heavy floods in Bulgaria exceeds 128m euros, according to the latest government report, presented Tuesday (26 July). The amount includes losses to infrastructure, personal property, real estate and crops. A team of experts from the EU is in Bulgaria assessing the damage. Brussels promised additional funding after a request from Sofia earlier this month. (bTV, Nova TV - 26/07/05) 
